#fields	domain	description
#
# IoT Security Gateway - Known-Bad Domain Names
#
# This file is read by Zeek's Input framework and automatically
# re-read when modified. I can update it without restarting Zeek.
#
# Format: one domain per line (lowercase), followed by a tab and
# a description. Lines starting with # are comments (except the
# #fields header which Zeek requires).
#
# Note: this complements AdGuard's DNS blocklists. AdGuard blocks
# queries at the DNS level (device gets no IP back). This file
# catches cases where a device might have cached an IP or received
# it through a non-DNS channel and attempts a connection to a
# domain that resolves to a known-bad IP.
#
# Sources for populating this file:
#   - Abuse.ch URLhaus (malware distribution domains)
#   - DGArchive (known DGA domains)
#   - Manual additions from incident investigations
#
# Example entries (replace with real IOCs):
# evil-c2-server.example.com	Example C2 domain
# malware-drop.example.net	Example malware distribution

evil-test-domain.local	Simulated malicious C2 domain for testing